Supply Chain & Logistics Performance Analytics
Project Overview
This project focuses on transforming raw supply chain data into actionable business intelligence. Using Tableau, I developed a comprehensive dashboard to monitor logistical efficiency, regional cost distributions, and supplier reliability. The goal is to provide stakeholders with a "single source of truth" for optimizing fulfillment strategies and reducing operational overhead.

Key Features & Visualizations
Executive KPI Header: Instant visibility into Total Cost per Unit ($16.89), Revenue Generated ($577k), and Order Fulfillment Rates (97.72%).

Regional Inventory Analysis: A grouped bar chart identifying the "Inventory Gap" across East, South, and West regions to pinpoint stock-out risks.

Cost Composition Pie Chart: A breakdown of Manufacturing, Shipping, Return, and Overhead costs to highlight the primary drivers of expenditure.

Fulfillment Trend Timeline: A custom-engineered line chart (using calculated date fields) that tracks Lead Time trends from January through November.

Carrier & Supplier Scorecards: Comparative analysis of Carrier performance (A, B, and C) and detailed Supplier metrics (Defect Rates vs. Lead Time).

Technical Skills Applied
Data Engineering: Created custom Order Date logic using INDEX() and DATEADD functions to generate time-series analysis from non-date datasets.

Advanced Calculations: Implemented Table Calculations for "Percent of Total" cost analysis and logic-based KPI cards.

UI/UX Design: Applied a professional dark-themed layout with a focus on visual hierarchy, color consistency, and scannable metrics.

Data Interactivity: Integrated global filters for Routes and Regions to allow for granular data exploration.

Tools Used
Tableau Desktop / Public

Data Transformation: Calculated Fields, Parameters, and Table Calculations.
